result.name: Lu Feng Restaurant

reviews.text:
Looked around the whole place and nearly missed the restaurant. For those who do not understand Chinese characters (which were all over the entrance of the restaurant), pay close attention to a tiny English translation in front of the lectern at the entrance that says "Lu Feng".  

While the reviews I read about this restaurant was already bad enough, the unwelcoming aura of the entrance for a non-Chinese like me completed my rejection.
Tourist trap. Unfriendly staff that talked about us behind our backs and provided no service at all. English was very bad too. Food was ok but very expensive.
Horrible service and food quality, doesn’t even taste like decent dim sum. Food took ages to come, wrong items, wrong bill and then overpriced. A real rip off place.
Can’t complain about the service there was none... sat drank some tea read the other reviews and left... went to wildfire downstairs will see how they go

The food I ordered was priced 5 times what it would cost elsewhere, which is for the view I suppose but it was poor to mediocre food. Then they added 68HKD ($7.45 USD) to the bill for dried fish and tea they put on the table without asking and I didn't touch. I was there at lunch and it was mostly empty, Now I see why. I never paid so much for so little at any other restaurant in the world. They win the prize for worst value ever. I will never eat at a restaurant without checking Google first again. The McDonald's would have been better by far.

result.name: Peak Tower

reviews.text: It's gives a fantastic view of Hong Kong. Please take a good camera with you. The classic tram ride through the backwards of some of the high rise buildings is another attraction. It's a real beauty. You won't get this experience in all the best of cities.

Awesome view of Hong Kong at the top. Scary bus ride down, unfortunately the tram was undergoing upgrading work during my visit. Worth the visit if you like to have a good view of the city, try going in the evening for day and night view.

The view from here was absolutely stunning! It does take a while to get up the mountain though, no matter which form of transport you choose to take. The area was perfect for pictures especially from a tourist view point.

The scenery is outstanding. You can either take the bus or the peak tram (currently is out of function due to maintenance) to get to the peak. Best time will be when the sky is clear to get good photos and evening to see the light show from the peak which will amaze you.
Absolutely incredible views of Hong Kong. Many restaurants and shops. I recommend going in the evening, the city view us even more impressive. Definitely on the to do list if visiting Hong Kong.

result.adr_address: 3A-B, Old Peak Rd, The Peak, 香港
result.formatted_address: 3A-B, Old Peak Rd, The Peak, 香港
result.name: Lu Feng Restaurant

reviews.text:
濫收費呃遊客欺人太甚！

本人與家人於今天中午在山頂凌霄閣二樓爐峰酒家用餐，酒家先奉上小食炸白飯魚一碟。上菜過程中無聲無息又奉上小食白飯魚一碟，向職員查詢，職員聲稱5人檯要買兩碟白飯魚小食。我向餐廳張經理查詢，張經理聲稱「全香港酒樓都係呢個做法」。我在香港生活了上十年，第一次遇到這種情況。我嘗試把第二碟白飯魚還給張經理，張經理說還給他還是要收費，難道這不是黑社會的強買強賣？！簡直欺人太甚！

隔壁桌的泰國遊客有5位，職員奉上三碟白飯魚，所以，5個人到底是兩碟還是三碟？我混亂了。
食物很美味， 但無奈服務態度太差， 經理級的服務態度非常差， 反而普通阿姐態度十分好。
爛到不行的餐廳，東西既沒特色又昂貴，各種陷阱點餐內容，要不是來玩的旁邊有家人真他媽給餐廳難看

Looked around the whole place and nearly missed the restaurant. For those who do not understand Chinese characters (which were all over the entrance of the restaurant), pay close attention to a tiny English translation in front of the lectern at the entrance that says "Lu Feng".  

While the reviews I read about this restaurant was already bad enough, the unwelcoming aura of the entrance for a non-Chinese like me completed my rejection.
Tourist trap. Unfriendly staff that talked about us behind our backs and provided no service at all. English was very bad too. Food was ok but very expensive.

result.adr_address: Victoria Peak, The Peak, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: Victoria Peak, The Peak, Hong Kong
result.name: Victoria Peak

html_attributions: สันติ พวงพิลา

reviews.text: You can have the best view of Hong Kong city from this peak . Would recommend going in clear and nice weather. In the morning it is nice because you can see the whole city very well and take good pictures. Loved the Tram experience. Also if you enjoy walking, you can hike for an hour and half through a jungle to reach there. Train takes very few minutes to reach at peak. Best restaurants at top.

If you continue up the hill from the tourist peak outlook, be sure to get the gardens for a beautiful view of the other side of the peak. And even more up the hill near the all the cell towers you'll get the best view. I don't recommend a night visit to this part, but the daytime view is breath taking.

My favourite place to hang out during a weekend in Hong Kong. Do consider taking a bus here instead of the tram - it is a much more scenic route if you’re not in a rush for time. Food and drink is rather expensive up there so full yourself up before going if you can.

You can have the best view of Hong Kong city from this peak . Would recommend going in clear and nice weather. In the morning it is nice because you can see the whole city very well and take good pictures. Loved the Tram experience. Also if you enjoy walking, you can hike for an hour and half through a jungle to reach there.

Big tourist spot. Lots of shops on a multi floor shopping centre. You can pay to go to the roof to get the best views but its cash only. There is a balcony that you can use for free near the top. I didnt go to the very top as I walked from the bottom
